    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Glow Plug Sleeve Removal</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage (if replacing glow plug sleeves in chassis), place a small plug into the
                    bottom of the glow plug sleeve before cutting removal threads. The plug will prevent small metal
                    chips from entering the combustion chamber.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2350456" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0850.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 164. Glow Plug Sleeve Remover - tap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate Glow Plug Sleeve Remover - tap .</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The glow plug sleeve is made of stainless steel. Lubrication of the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover -
                        tap is required, otherwise excessive force will be necessary to get the tap started.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install tool to cut threads into the glow plug sleeve. Cut threads at least 1/2 inch deep to
                accommodate the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover tool.
            </para>
            <figure id="f2350457" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/d0849.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 165. Glow Plug Sleeve Remover - tap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread the Glow Plug Sleeve Remover into the sleeve.</para>
            <figure id="f2350458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/d0852.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 166. Glow Plug Sleeve Remover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350459" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0853.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 167. Removing glow plug sleeve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a wrench to thread tool into sleeve until sleeve is extracted.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove glow plug sleeve.</para>
            <figure id="f2350460" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/d0854.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 168. Glow plug sleeve removed</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2350461" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/d0851.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 169. Cleaning glow plug bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean glow plug bore with Glow Plug Sleeve Seat Wire Brush .</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
